Mr Kagwe earlier said there was no need for Kenya to close its airspace due to the new variant of Covid-19.The CS said Kenya will make decisions based on scientific advice as well as any additional advice from WHO. Travellers from Britain should have negative Covid-19 test results within a 96-hour period from the time they tested to the time they will be arriving in the country, according to the new guidelines by the Ministry of Health.
Responding to the Nation question on why the government has not suspended flights from Britain yet other countries have, Health Cabinet Secretary Mutahi Kagwe said Kenya has put in strict measures which were never in place in the said countries.



